data-triple-N3.o: "The J. League Division 2 or J2 League is the second division of Japan Professional Football League and is the second-tier professional association football league in Japan. Currently, J. League Division 2 is the second level of the Japanese association football league system. The first tier is represented by J. League Division 1. Second-tier club football has existed in Japan since 1972; however, it was only professionalized during the 1999 season with ten clubs."@en
